oads\/2020\/03\/23121929\/things-to-do-krabi-Rock-climbing-30x23.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/23121929\/things-to-do-krabi-Rock-climbing.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3>8. Koh Lipe&#xA0;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Koh Lipe might be Thailand&#x2019;s best-kept secret. The small, but perfectly formed, white-sand beached island is a 7-hour journey from Krabi, so it is recommended to visit for a few days. Spend your days walking along the beaches stretching over the length of the island and enjoying island vibes. Koh Lipe is well worth the trip.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--readmore \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--readmore\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/thailand\/koh-lipe\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Paradise Island Koh Lipe, Thailand (opens in a new tab)\" data-rich-text-format-boundary=\"true\">Paradise Island Koh Lipe, Thailand<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div>